                  <h6>General Booking and Financial Terms</h6>
                  <h6>Damage to Jet Skis - BareJet Ski Rentals</h6>
                  <p>As a Renter, you are responsible for leaving the Jet Ski in the condition it was in &nbsp;at delivery, fair wear and tear excepted. You acknowledge and agree that, as a Renter, you are responsible for your own acts and omissions and are also responsible for the acts and omissions of any individuals who you invite to, or otherwise provide access to the Jet Ski. In the event that following the conclusion of a rental, a Jet Ski Owner claims &nbsp;that the Jet Ski has been damaged during the rental and provides evidence of damage, including but not limited to, photographs, or other evidence you agree to pay the cost of repairing the damage or replacing the damaged items with equivalent items. After being notified of the claim and given forty eight (48) hours to respond, the payment will be charged to and taken from the credit card on file in your Skiski Account. Skiski also reserves the right to charge the credit card on file in your Skiski Account, or otherwise collect payment from you and pursue any avenues available to Skiski in this regard, including using Security Deposits, in situations in which you have been determined, in Skiski’s sole discretion, to have damaged the Jet Ski, including, but not limited to, in relation to any payment requests made by Jet Ski Owner, and in relation to any payments made by Skiski to Jet Ski Owners. If we are unable to charge the credit card on file or otherwise collect payment from you, you agree to remit payment for any damage to the Jet Ski to the applicable Jet Ski Owner or to Skiski (if applicable).</p>
                  <p>Both Renter and Jet Ski Owner agree to cooperate with and assist Skiski in good faith, and to provide Skiski with such information and take such actions as may be reasonably requested by Skiski, in connection with any complaints or claims made by Members relating to Jet Skis or any personal or other property located at a Jet Ski or with respect to any investigation undertaken by Skiski or a representative of Skiski regarding use or abuse of the Site, Application or the Services. If you are a Renter, upon Skiski's reasonable request, and to the extent you are reasonably able to do so, you agree to participate in mediation or similar resolution process with a Jet Ski Owner, at no cost to you, which process will be conducted by Skiski or a third party selected by Skiski, with respect to losses for which the Jet Ski Owner is requesting payment from Skiski under these terms. &nbsp;When an insurance claim is filed the Renter’s Security Deposit will be captured and if applicable used to cover the insurance deductible.</p>
                  <h6>Cancellations and Refunds</h6>
                  <p>If, as a Renter, you cancel your requested booking before the requested booking is confirmed by an Owner, Skiski will cancel any pre-authorization to your credit card and/or refund any nominal amounts charged to your credit card in connection with the requested booking within a commercially reasonable time. If, as a Renter, you wish to cancel a confirmed booking made via the Services, either prior to or after arriving at the Jet Ski, the cancellation policy of the Owner contained in the applicable Listing will apply to such cancellation. Our ability to refund the Jet Ski Fees and other amounts charged to you will depend upon the terms of the applicable cancellation policy. Details regarding refunds and cancellation policies are available via the Services.</p>
                  <p>If an Owner cancels a confirmed booking made via the Services, (i) Skiski will refund the Total Fees for such booking to the applicable Renter within a commercially reasonable time of the cancellation and (ii) the Renter may receive an email or other communication from Skiski containing alternative available Listings and other related information. If the Renter requests a booking from one of the alternative Listings and the Owner associated with such alternative Listing confirms the Renter’s requested booking, then the Renter agrees to pay Skiski the Total Fees relating to the confirmed booking for the Jet Ski in the alternative Listing, in accordance with these Terms. If an Owner cancels a confirmed booking and you, as a Renter, have not received an email or other communication from Skiski, please contact our support team via a <a target="_blank" href="">support ticket</a>.</p>
